Cyber Monday 2019 is here, and many South African retailers and service providers are running deals where consumers can enjoy big discounts. Cyber Monday is the first Monday after Black Friday and was initially established to encourage people to shop online. The term was first used in a Shop.org press release entitled “Cyber Monday”, adding that the day is “quickly becoming one of the biggest online shopping days of the year”. Cyber Monday is now a marketing term which is used by online retailers across the globe to drive online sales. While a few stores launch specific Cyber Monday deals, most South African companies have decided to run their Black Friday sales into Monday. This means that most promotions in South Africa run from 29 November (Black Friday) to 2 December (Cyber Monday). Here are some of the prominent South African retailers where you can find discounts on tech products and online services on Cyber Monday. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-328401" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Takealot-Sale.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Takealot-Sale.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Takealot-Sale-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Takealot-Sale-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-330905" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/MyBroadband-Cyber-Monday-article-banner-640x430.gif" alt="MyBroadband Cyber Monday article banner" width="640" height="430" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-238380" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Rugged-SA-Header.jpg" alt="Rugged SA Header" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Rugged-SA-Header.jpg